g.title: 程序.29
g.desc: 1. Nothing Frame : A frame, 96 lines/1.44"&2", 176 lines/2.7"...
g.text: 1. Nothing Frame : A frame, 96 lines/1.44"&2", 176 lines/2.7", whose all D(x,y) are N(01). Scan Bytes operate normally. Scan lines are still turned on sequentially. This frame will make the image more uniform.2. Dummy Line : A line whose all Data Bytes are 0x55 and Scan Bytes are 0x00. Clear the register data before power off.3. BORDER : For implement this function, users need to use a pin to control from Microcontroller. When = 0, the BORDER is ON and write to white. When = 1,the BORDER is OFF. The reason for using BORDER is to keep a sharp border and not have a charge on the Eink particles . Voltage too long on these will produce a gray effect which is the optimal for long term operation. BORDER is needed in V220 FPL and V110 FPL. 4. External Discharge : For implement this function, users need to use a pin from Microcontroller to control. This is important to avoid vertical lines.5.If you use the Flash memory for pattern store, please recheck flash in this phase and verify the old image flash is erased.
